    "group": "English Docs",
    "title": "9. How to use community sources correctly",
    "summary": "Correct use: use UberGuidoZ/Flipper as an ecosystem map use Flipper-IRDB for IR-library discovery use jamisonderek for developer teaching and debugging insight use awesome-flipperzero as a discovery layer use smaller pro",
    "text": "FlipperZero AI Pack (English) 9. How to use community sources correctly Correct use: use UberGuidoZ/Flipper as an ecosystem map use Flipper-IRDB for IR-library discovery use jamisonderek for developer teaching and debugging insight use awesome-flipperzero as a discovery layer use smaller project repos as examples of real app structure, peripheral patterns, and workflow ideas Incorrect use: treating community repos as official API docs treating community firmware as the definition of official behavior treating a single successful project as a platform-wide rule",
